# Arbitrary environment variables to inject into the container.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored) and add KEY=VALUE lines. run.sh loads it
# via `docker --env-file` only when the file exists; a comments-only file is a
# no-op, so it is safe for `make init` to create.
#
# IMPORTANT — `docker --env-file` parsing differs from shells and dotenv libs:
#   - Values are LITERAL: `FOO="bar"` injects the quotes too. Do NOT quote.
#   - No interpolation: `FOO=$BAR` / `FOO=${BAR}` are literal, not expanded.
#   - No multiline values; `#` comments must be on their own line.
#   - A bare line `FOO` (no `=`) pulls FOO from the launch environment.
#
# Internal vars (HOME, COLORTERM, MCP_GH_BEARER, CONTAINER_OPEN_PORTS) are set
# after this file on the docker command line and cannot be overridden here.
#
# Examples (uncomment and edit):
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@localhost:5432/app
# MY_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxx
# Forward a var already exported in your launch shell (no value, just the name):
# SOME_TOKEN
